        <h1 class="title">OUR STORY</h1>
        <div class="statement-line2"></div>
        <br>
        <p>
            Many homeless individuals face life-threatening risks like hypothermia and frostbite during winter due to inadequate shelter access and poorly constructed cold-weather response plans. 
            Jen, once homeless herself, experienced these dangers firsthand and tragically lost seven friends to freezing temperatures. 
            Determined to help, she launched the Turtle Shelter Project in 2017 with Angela Roth.
            Using Jim Phillips' foam clothing technology, they designed affordable, high-tech foam vests that retain warmth even when wet and keep wearers warm in temperatures as low as -10°F. 
            These portable and durable Turtle Shelters provide life-saving insulation for those without access to shelters. 
            Communities can request these vests or rally groups—friends, businesses, churches, or clubs—to make and distribute them. 
            Together, we can fight the cold, save lives, and offer hope to those in need.
        </p>
    </section>


